Subject: Re: [VB] Overheating / to those who use Gene Berg, dipstick oil

Not the pulley, the fan belt.

The thicker alternator fan belt sits low on the alternator pulley (it
requires few shims inside). It sits low because it is thicker than the
generator belt. Since it sits low it makes the alternator/fan spin
faster.

John Conolly explained the trick to me

- Arnaud


